    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is mitigated by strong inter-laboratory reproducibility (CV<3%) and the prescriptive nature of ASTM F1717, which mandates a single canonical test condition. All three QoIs satisfy E/uval<1.96 and <10% difference acceptance criteria. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support regulatory use of the FEA framework for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
